# CGEM IDE key bindings
# Format: <action> <key>
#
# Supported keys: F1-F12, Ctrl+Letter
# (Ctrl+Shift, Shift+Alt and similar combos are not supported — unreliable in
# terminals and the Windows console, same reason vi/nano stick to simpler keys.)
#
# Ctrl+letter layout (one action per letter):
#   A select-all   B generate*   C copy      D free
#   E free         F find      G goto      H free
#   I (tab)        J free      K format    L (clear screen in shell)
#   M (enter)      N free      O open*     P free
#   Q quit         R free      S save      T free
#   U paste formatted   V paste   W free      X cut
#   Y redo         Z undo
# * Ctrl+B is Generate for now; action.build (compile) will reuse it later.
# * O reserved for action.open.
#
# F2-F6 open top-level menus only.
#
# Function keys: F1-F7 are used by default; F8, F9, F11, and F12 are free
# for custom bindings. Do not bind F10 — on Windows consoles (including XP) it
# opens the system menu and the key may never reach the editor. Rebind F10 only
# at your own risk (Linux terminals are usually fine).

menu.file F2
menu.edit F3
menu.build F4
menu.options F5
menu.help F6

action.save Ctrl+S
action.generate Ctrl+B
action.quit Ctrl+Q
action.copy Ctrl+C
action.cut Ctrl+X
action.paste Ctrl+V
action.paste_formatted Ctrl+U
action.select_all Ctrl+A
action.undo Ctrl+Z
action.redo Ctrl+Y
action.find Ctrl+F
action.find_next F7
action.goto_line Ctrl+G
action.goto_definition F12
action.rename F8
action.format Ctrl+K
action.help F1

# Fixed editor keys (not remappable — terminal Tab / Shift+Tab):
#   Tab         increase nesting (4 spaces) or accept keyword hint
#   Shift+Tab   decrease nesting (4 spaces)

# action.build Ctrl+B
# action.open Ctrl+O
